I"s<h1 id="marinated-chicken-with-tomato-mozarella-salad">Marinated chicken with tomato mozarella salad</h1>

<p>Let’s see how to cook your chosen dish.</p>

<h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h2>

<p>Here is what you need to have at home.</p>

<ol>
  <li>1kg, chicken thighs;</li>
  <li>1, baking bag with marinating seasoning;</li>
  <li>4, tomatos, sliced;</li>
  <li>150g, mozarella, sliced;</li>
  <li>4 cloves, garlic, finely chopped;</li>
  <li>2 splashes, oliv oil;</li>
  <li>2 splashes, balsamic vinegar;</li>
  <li>1 handful, basil.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="preparation">Preparation</h2>

<p>Time: Takes as long as it takes.<br />
Serves: Make sure to share, and buy for your pals.</p>

<p>Here are the steps to cook the meal. Enjoy!</p>

<ol>
  <li>Start playing music in the background.</li>
  <li>Pore a glass of drink for the chef.</li>
  <li>Marinate the chicken, and let it rest while you prepare the salad.</li>
  <li>In a dish, lay down a layer of sliced tomato. Add the mozarella slices on top.</li>
  <li>Now add the basil, garlic, a bit of oil and balsamic vinegar.</li>
  <li>Repeat the previous step for an other layer.</li>
  <li>While the salad is resting, place the marinated chicken in the baking bag, and seal it. Don’t forget to punch a few holes to let the steam escape.</li>
  <li>bake for 45-50 minutes on 180 degrees.</li>
  <li>Serve the chicken with the tomato salad.</li>
</ol>

